President Museveni explained in a [television interview](http://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-35601220) “Some people misuse those pathways. You know how they misuse them – telling lies… if you want a right then use it properly.”

Ugandans rapidly turned to VPN software and other proxy tools in order to bypass the blocking, with an [estimated 1.4 million downloads](https://twitter.com/cobbo3/status/700425026953150464) for Android. Psiphon use increased dramatically as netizens connected through the circumvention network to restore their right to communicate and access information.

